---
import SectionTitle from "./SectionTitle.astro";
import Playground from "./Playground.svelte";
---

<section class="sect" id="playground">
  <div class="container-xl">
    <SectionTitle
      eyebrow="compose a stream, watch the bits."
      eyebrowEm="Playground."
      title={`Poke it. <em>Break it.</em>`}
      description="Add sections, change the values, and watch the token and the underlying bits update live. It all runs right here in your browser."
    />

    <div class="reveal">
      <Playground client:visible />
    </div>

    <p class="pg-foot">
      The decoder never needs the schema. It tells you the mode and the width,
      and you tell <em>it</em> what the chunks mean.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pg-foot {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: var(--color-ink-300);
    max-width: 60ch;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .pg-foot em {
    color: var(--color-signal-300);
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 15.5px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
</style>
